README for coreutils


IMPORTANT NOTES

  Coreutils 9.11 enables Y2038 support by default and aborts the configure
  stage if a 64-bit `time_t` is unavailable.

  On this platform (ARMv6 + glibc 2.22), `time_t` is still 32-bit, so the
  configure check fails with:

    checking for gcc option to support timestamps after 2038... support not detected
    configure: error: could not enable timestamps after mid-January 2038.

  To preserve compatibility with glibc 2.22, this port passes:

    --disable-year2038

  This is a compatibility workaround only. It does not change the existing
  aBI or behavior of the system, which already uses a 32-bit `time_t`.
